<TITLE> Sahara briefs House on mutiny </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 26 (bdnews24.com)Home minister Sahara Khatun told parliament Thursday all the rebellious BDR members had laid down their arms and returned to barracks. She said situation at the BDR headquarters was "totally under control" of the government. The minister, who led a series of crucial negotiations with the mutineers, said Dhaka Metropolitan Police had been maintaining security at the BDR headquarters. "By 7:30pm [Thursday], all the rebel BDR members responded to the call of the prime minister and deposited their arms and ammunition to the armoury," she told parliament in a statement on an urgent issue. "The key of the armoury is now with me." "All of them have returned to the barracks. "The situation in the BDR headquarters is peaceful and totally under government's control." The MPs in attendence thanked the minister by thumping desks. The minister said the prime minister, the senior ministers and the MPs had talked several times with the "angry" BDR members to resolve the crisis. "On Wednesday, some angry BDR members entered into the Darbar Hall while the BDR week was on. The angry BDR members demanded that their demands were met. "Firing took place there and there were some incidents of casualties at the Darbar Hall," the minister said. Some civilians were also killed, she said, but did not say how many people were killed. Earlier, the main opposition BNP MPs demanded suspension of parliament to discuss the mutiny in BDR. But speaker Hamid rejected their demands and assured the House that the home minister would issue a statement.
